                     <interp inst="def1-137-18571214" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-137-18571214" type="surname" value="SAMBIO"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-137-18571214" type="given" value=""></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">SAMBIO</hi>
                  </persName> (<hi rend="italic">a black</hi>)<rs id="t18571214-137-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18571214-137-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18571214-137-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="burglary"></interp> (20), Burglariously breaking and entering the dwelling house of <persName id="t18571214-name-220" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18571214-name-220" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18571214-name-220" type="surname" value="MARKS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18571214-name-220" type="given" value="HARRIS"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18571214-137-offence-1 t18571214-name-220"></join>Harris Marks</persName>, and stealing therein 3 shirts, 2 jackets, 7 handkerchiefs, and other articles, value 5<hi rend="italic">l</hi>., his property.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>(<hi rend="italic">The evidence was interpreted to the prisoner.</hi>)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18571214-name-221" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18571214-name-221" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18571214-name-221" type="surname" value="MARKS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18571214-name-221" type="given" value="HARRIS"></interp>HARRIS MARKS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a clothier, of No. 236, High Street, Shadwell. On Saturday night, 28th Nov., a policeman came to me, with the prisoner</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="185712140040"></xptr>
               <p>and some jackets, which were mine, and which I had seen safe on the Thurs<lb></lb>day, before I went to bed—I missed them on Friday morning at 5 o'clock, when I came down and found my sitting room window open—I went into the kitchen, and found a skylight broken, and the door which leads to the yard unbolted, which had been safe when I went to bed the night before—the skylight was broken sufficient for a person to get in—I was the last per<lb></lb>son up—the skylight and everything was then perfectly safe.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18571214-name-222" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18571214-name-222" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18571214-name-222" type="surname" value="PAWSEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18571214-name-222" type="given" value="ISAAC"></interp>ISAAC PAWSEY</persName>
                  </hi>. (<hi rend="italic">Policeman, K</hi> 53). I received information, and on Sa<lb></lb>turday, 28th Nov., went to a house in Blue Gate Fields, Shoreditch—I saw the prisoner there, and asked him in English where he got the clothes that he was wearing—from what I could understand, he said that he bought them at Liverpool six months ago—I went for the prosecutor, who identified the clothes, and then took the prisoner into custody—he had got them all on—the prosecutor's house is in the parish of St. Paul, Shadwell.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18571214-name-223" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18571214-name-223" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18571214-name-223" type="surname" value="MARKS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18571214-name-223" type="given" value="HARRIS"></interp>HARRIS MARKS</persName>
                  </hi>. <hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi> These clothes are mine—at the time he says he bought them he was in prison—his own clothes were found in a closet at my house.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> When the constable took me, I had bought the clothes about a fortnight previous of a Chinaman, named Hah Coey, for 27<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18571214-name-224" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18571214-name-224" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18571214-name-224" type="surname" value="BIDGOOD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18571214-name-224" type="given" value="PETER"></interp>PETER BIDGOOD</persName>
                  </hi>. (<hi rend="italic">Policeman, K</hi> 168). I took possession of some clothes found at Mr. Marks's, on the tiles, where the skylight was broken—I did not take them to the prisoner, but I knew they were his, for I saw them on his back.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <rs id="t18571214-137-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
